Why?
Let me tell you about an experiment carried out in 2014 at the University of Virginia in Charlottesville.
Professor Timothy Wilson gathered a few dozen students and gave them the simplest task in the world: to be alone for 15 minutes, with their thoughts, in an empty room, except for a button which they can push to get an electric shock.
They knew.
They signed a paper that said that they prefer giving money rather than getting an electric shock. We can understand that.
But, but, but ... 15 minutes,15 minutes, that's long.
