That's really incredible.
I never stopped thinking about this.
Why? What risk was she talking about?
What is this risk?
Even today, if I wanted to change my life, my path, my job, where would be the risk?
What is the problem in my head?
What is the problem in our heads?
Where's the problem?
The problem, because I've pondered over this question a lot, is our imagination.
It's what differentiates us from the animals.
That is to say, we humans, we map things out, we anticipate, we are the kings of the cause and effect, we know what is going to happen.
We are the Nostradamuses of our lives.
Why?
Because we have "the vision."
