I slept there during the week.
We studied till late at night, 9 or 10pm.
I was tremendously interested in my studies.
The day was dedicated to reading the Koran or explaining the Koran text.
I didn't learn to write or to count, but it's a great opportunity to attend a Koranic school!
I was learning... and my parents were proud of me.
I am an imam which means I can lead the prayer in a mosque.
In the madrassah, many armed Taliban came.
Everybody was scared.
